    <item>
      <title>Bare-Metal &#34;Hello World&#34; on RISC-V - Part 2</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/riscv-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 01:08:05 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/riscv-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;project-structure&#34;&gt;Project Structure&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;riscv-uart/
├── Makefile       # Build rules and QEMU invocation
├── start.S        # Assembly entry point (_start)
├── linker.ld      # Memory map and section placement
└── main.c         # The C &amp;#34;application&amp;#34;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;Four files. That is the entire project. Each one plays a distinct, irreplaceable role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-makefile&#34;&gt;The Makefile&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-makefile&#34; data-lang=&#34;makefile&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;CC&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; riscv64-unknown-elf-gcc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;CFLAGS&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    -march&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;rv32i &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    -mabi&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;ilp32 &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    -nostdlib &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    -ffreestanding
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;all&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;CC&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;CFLAGS&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        start.S main.c &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        -T linker.ld &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        -o kernel.elf
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;run&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    qemu-system-riscv32 &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        -machine virt &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        -nographic &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        -bios none &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        -kernel kernel.elf
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;dissecting-the-flags&#34;&gt;Dissecting the flags&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;code&gt;-march=rv32i&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; — Target the RV32I instruction set. The compiler will only emit instructions from this subset. Using a 64-bit instruction on a 32-bit target would be a hard error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Bare-Metal &#34;Hello World&#34; on RISC-V - Part 1</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/riscv-1/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 00:51:05 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/riscv-1/</guid>
      <description>Learn the fundamentals of bare-metal programming on RISC-V with a hands-on hello world example.</description>
